The failure is that `StateMachine.Repo` — the module the test harness (and the environment's config/migration/supervision) key on — is never defined as an Ecto repo, so `Ecto.Adapters.SQL.Sandbox.start_owner!/2` blows up with `:undef` on `get_dynamic_repo/0`. The environment configures, migrates and supervises a repo *by that module name*, but the module definition itself has to exist. Defining `StateMachine.Repo` as a real Ecto repo fixes every test at once. I'm changing only `solution.ex`.

